3530,Stars On Stripes Football Game,['Dice Rolling'],['Sports'],"Game was produced by Stars on Stripes Co, Incorporated , 406 McKenna Building, Pittsburgh, PA. On the box it says The GRANT Building.<br/><br/>A simple simulation of an football game. The game has taken 14 years to develop, but it is so simplified you can learn to play it in just one minute.<br/>The equipment consists of two boards, three wooden dice, five wooden pegs, a &quot;Bakelite&quot; football and a 10 yard marker.<br/>First - Call your play (line plunge, off tackle, end run...)<br/>Second - Throw three dice and the results are always read from low to the high number. 5-4-1 will read 145.<br/>Third - look on the Signal chart to see what happens to the ball.<br/>The player must gain 10 yards in four downs or lose the ball.<br/>When the ball touches or goes over the Goal Line it is a Touchdown.<br/><br/>I have the Game and played the game with my friend Mike about every night doing the football seasons, from 1943-1952.  I feel it was a fantastic game and very simple to play, and there were over 1500 different combinations of plays you could make, which made it a very realistic game.  If you would like a copy of the game, just e-mail me, you would need to suppy about 5 push pins, and a 10 yard marker, and marker for the football.  This game is very rare, as it was made in 1941, but to me still a great game, also you would need 3 dice.<br/>jdlaughead@gmail.com<br/><br/>",1941,,,
