3540,Tic Tac Chec,"['Grid Movement', 'Pattern Building']",['Abstract Strategy'],"Tic Tac Chec is both a chess teaching tool and a clever strategy game.  Each player has four pieces: a knight, a rook, a bishop and a pawn.  The object of the game is to be the first to align your pieces in a vertical, horizontal or diagonal row.  Play starts on an empty 4 x 4 board and players take turns placing a piece on any open square.  Once at least three pieces are placed per player, they may move a piece, capture a piece or place their remaining piece.  Captured pieces are returned to their player and may be replayed on any open square.<br/><br/>",1995,,,
3541,Noble Celts,['Grid Movement'],['Abstract Strategy'],"Noble Celts is a circular chess boardgame that is played exactly like regulation Chess.  There are 64 circles corresponding to the 64 squares.  Diagonal moves are made along lines that spiral into and out of the center of the board.  Pieces are set up along the outside of the circle and around the center ring, and play is inward or outward.  The lack of a side edge to what, if uncurled, would be a normal chess board makes for very exciting play.<br/><br/>",1993,,,
