3946,CheHops,['Pattern Building'],['Abstract Strategy'],"Pyramid<br/><br/>Contents:  24 pyramids, 12 black and 12 gold<br/><br/>Goal of the game:  The winner is the first player to place 5 pyramids of their color in a row, either horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.<br/><br/>The first player places one of his pyramids on the table.  The second player places one of his pyramids in such a way that it is touching one of the four edges or four corners of Player A&rsquo;s pyramid. Play continues in this manner, each player following the other by placing one pyramid in turn.<br/><br/>If after all 24 pyramids are played and neither player successfully places 5 pyramids in a row then play continues but players remove and replace one of their already placed pyramids on their turn. Play continues until one player has placed 5 pyramids in a row.<br/><br/>This game was released by Hasbo in Germany and the US.<br/><br/>",1978,,,
