h and Italians are represented.<br/><br/>TB-22 Base Game(Rules Versions potentially from 1.x - 3.x)<br/>TB-22b Base Game (Rules Version 4.x)<br/><br/>Expansions for Advanced Tobruk: Tank Battles in North Africa Include - <br/>TB-23 - Advanced Tobruk Gamers Guide<br/><br/>TB-24 - ATS Expansion 1: Wavells 30,000 - 12 Scenarios, 30 new counters, 3 terrain overlays, 1 new AFV Card.  (1940/41 ending with Beda Fomm). <br/>TB-25 - ATS Expansion 2: Benghazi Handicap - 12 Scenarios, 30 new counters, 1 new terrain overlay.   (March/April 1941 Britsh vs. Italians)<br/>TB-26 - ATS Expansion 3: Devil's Garden - 12 Scenarios, 37 counters, 4 new AFV cards. (El Alamein 1942 British vs. Germans and Italians)<br/>TB-27 - ATS Expansion 4: Blunted Sword - 12 Scenarios, 37 Counters, 7 New AFV Cards. (Tunisia British vs. Germans and Italians).<br/>TB-28 - ATS Expansion 5a: Kasserine and Beyond - 12 Scenarios, 310 Counters, 12 new AFV. (Tunisia American and French vs. Germans and Italians plus American vs. French)<br/>TB-29 - ATS Expansion 5b: Torch to Tunisia - 12 Scenarios, 1942-1943 (French Morocco Tunis, American vs French, American, French vs. German, German vs French).<br/>TB-30 - ATS Expansion 6: Killing Fields - 13 Scenarios, 1941-1943 (British vs German and Italians, American vs Italian).<br/><br/>In 2009:  The publisher indicated that additional expansions for the North Africa Campaign were to be Published.   TB-31 thru TB-34.<br/><br/>A total of 109 Scenarios make up the base game with the expansions.   An additional 4 scenarios (two by CH were available for download and two in Fire and Movement issue 145.<br/><br/>This is the classic version of ATS (pre-version 2014).    Critical hit has re-implemented the North Africa Campaign with its 2014 Ruleset and updated maps, counters and expansions.   Unfortunately the naming convention is not consistent and republished titles are not always named the same.   For instance the expansion Facing the Blitz is the exact same game as ATS Briefing #1.   A clear and concise summary of each expansion does not currently exist that points out duplication.<br/><br/>",2002,,,
