4083,Hi-Spot,"['Pattern Building', 'Tile Placement']",['Abstract Strategy'],"A game for 2-4, where players place tiles of clear plastic with dots on them on a playing board with nine positions. Each turn the player can place a tile in a clear position, or over the stacked tiles in an filled position provided that the dots on the tile do not overlap those on the tiles already played. Once all 9 possible dots are placed in each position the stacked tiles are removed for reuse and the position is cleared for new tile placements. Points are awarded to the player after each turn based on the number of dots in the position that the tile was placed. The first player to score 200 points wins the game.<br/><br/>Identical in materials but different in rules is Topminos.<br/><br/>",1969,,,
