4701,King of the Hill,['Roll / Spin and Move'],"[""Children's Game"", 'Racing']","Players take turns moving their marble to the top of the plastic mountain.  If a marble lands on a hole, it is dropped in and comes out in a random fashion at a lower level cave.  Marbles making it to the crown on top are dropped in, and will usually fall through to a lower level, but if the crown pops up, the player wins.  Instead of a die, the game has a unique hourglass shaped teeter-totter piece which, when flipped, causes a small marble (keeping with the marble theme) to fall through a series of pegs to one of 6 slots at the bottom marked with numbers.<br/><br/>",1958,,,
