4910,Deluxe Wheel of Fortune,['Spelling'],"['Movies / TV / Radio theme', 'Word Game']","Editions vary, but a familiar phrase or name is hidden on the gameboard. Either the letters represented by cards are face down or the letters are covered by slides. Before guessing letter, a player must spin the eponymous Wheel of Fortune to determine how much each letter, if revealed, is worth to one&rsquo;s account. Every spin is risk, however, because one could lose a turn or spin &quot;Bankrupt&quot; which means lose a turn and forfeit one&rsquo;s earnings! Consonants only can be guessed after spinning the wheel; vowels can be guessed at a cost.<br/><br/>A player can continue taking one&rsquo;s turn until a wrong guess is made and then the turn passes to the next player. Only the player who solves the word puzzle can keep the earnings made for that round. The player who has made the most money after a predetermined number of puzzles is the winner.<br/><br/>The game is a faithful adaptation to the wildly popular television series.<br/><br/>",1975,,,
4911,Wacky Wizard Game,"['Role Playing', 'Roll / Spin and Move', 'Set Collection']","['Dice', 'Movies / TV / Radio theme']","Wacky Wizard is a game in which players assume the roles of unfortunate victims of a looney wizard.  Changed into one of six types of animals (bats, spiders, snakes, etc), the players must gather the ingredients necessary to break the spell over them.<br/><br/>Taking turns to play, players move their pieces on the board based on the flicking of a spinner.  Ingredient discs are placed at the edges of the board and a player's piece must land exactly on the spaces to collect the items.  To break the spell over them, the creatures need to collect two different ingredients with their own symbols (e.g. a Turtle would require an Eye of Newt and a Fingernail of Newt).  If the spinner lands on the Wacky Wizard symbol, the player draws a Wizard Spell Card, which will turn his or her playing piece into another creature (and thereby changing his or her winning conditions).<br/><br/>The first player to break the enchantment over his or her piece wins and ends the game.<br/><br/>",1977,,,
